  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "Hand-drawn anime, also known as traditional animation, encompasses a wide variety of series and films. While the industry has widely transitioned to digital techniques, many notable works still retain that hand-drawn aesthetic. Here are some prominent hand-drawn anime:\n\n### Classic Films and Series\n1. **Studio Ghibli Works**:\n   - **Spirited Away** (2001)\n   - **My Neighbor Totoro** (1988)\n   - **Princess Mononoke** (1997)\n   - **Howl's Moving Castle** (2004)\n\n2. **Akira** (1988) - A groundbreaking cyberpunk film known for its detailed art and animation.\n\n3. **Ghost in the Shell** (1995) - A classic cyberpunk anime film that has influenced countless works in the genre.\n\n4. **Sailor Moon** (1992-1997) - A classic magical girl series known for its iconic hand-drawn look.\n\n5. **Neon Genesis Evangelion** (1995-1996) - An influential mecha anime that features hand-drawn animation and a deep, complex narrative.\n\n### Recent Works\n1. **Your Name** (Kimi no Na wa) (2016) - A romantic fantasy film with stunning visuals and emotional storytelling.\n\n2. **Weathering With You** (Tenki no Ko) (2019) - Another film by Makoto Shinkai, known for its beautiful animation.\n\n3. **A Silent Voice** (Koe no Katachi) (2016) - A poignant narrative about redemption and bullying, featuring a hand-drawn style.\n\n4. **The Tale of the Princess Kaguya** (2013) - A unique film by Studio Ghibli that uses a watercolor aesthetic.\n\n5. **Promare** (2019) - A vibrant film with striking character design and dynamic animation.\n\n### Ongoing and Recent Series\n1. **Attack on Titan** (Shingeki no Kyojin) - While some elements are done with CGI, the series has a strong hand-drawn aesthetic.\n\n2. **Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba** - The anime features a mix of traditional hand-drawn animation and digital effects but retains a hand-drawn core style.\n\n3. **Mob Psycho 100** (2016-2022) - A supernatural comedy-drama with a unique artistic style that incorporates hand-drawn animation.\n\n4. **Vinland Saga** (2019-present) - A historical anime that combines stunning hand-drawn visuals with a gripping narrative.\n\n5. **The Promised Neverland** (2019-2021) - Known for its unique and dark storytelling style, executed through traditional means.\n\n### Notable Mentions\n- **Cowboy Bebop** (1998) - A classic series that has stood the test of time with its unique style and storytelling.\n- **Samurai Champloo** (2004) - Combines historical elements with a modern aesthetic and music influences.\n\n### Conclusion\nHand-drawn anime remains an integral part of the medium's charm. While many productions now incorporate digital techniques, the hand-drawn style is still cherished, and several recent works sustain that tradition. Whether in films or series, the artistry of hand-drawn anime continues to captivate audiences worldwide.",
